mast ★☆☆☆☆1.N-COUNT 可数名词船桅;桅杆 The masts of a boat are the tall upright poles that support its sails.
2.N-COUNT 可数名词天线杆 A radio mast is a tall upright structure that is used to transmit radio or television signals.
3. to nail your colours to the mast→see: colour; to nail your colours to someone's mast→see: colour;
